<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I agree with you in the fear that there will be too many of one class.  This is for a good reason and not for overpowering.  You see, soooooo many ppl have wanted to play a game with effective assassins... and now that there is one, everyone wants to be one.  So many ppl want to be one, in fact, that I no longer have any desire to choose the assassin class cuz I don't like blending into crowds.  I was origionally going to start a sorta assassin's guild (not assassin specific, tho) but now I don't really know, they seem like they may be all too common.  This is unfortunate, but the assassin system in this game will be so awesome you'd be crazy not to try it out.  I think I'm prolly gonna be a character class that no one seems to want to play cuz EQ overpowered it... yep, the necromancer.<P>As for your other concerns, I'm sure that they considered these.  The Cos. Serv. on SB seems pretty cool, and I think they'll handle problems when they see them.  They want to make a good game and not just a way to get money.<P>-Deadmeat</FONT>
